                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="arnold_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">(1741-1801) an American general who <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/betray#betray_sng_1" title="betrayed definition"><span class="ndv">betrayed</span></a> his country in the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-american-revolution#the_american_revolution_topg_1" title="American Revolution definition"><span class="ndv">American Revolution</span></a>. Although at first he fought bravely and won battles for the Americans, he tried in 1780 to give the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/fort#fort_topg_1" title="fort definition"><span class="ndv">fort</span></a> at <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/west-point" title="West Point definition"><span class="ndv">West Point</span></a>, which he commanded, to the British. He failed and escaped to London. His name is still used by Americans to mean somebody who betrays their country.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
